    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <p>
                    <pb n="27r" facs="http://content.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de/dms/PPN838243592/1200/0/00000055.jpg"/>
                    <hi rendition="#uu">
                        <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/1252558">Himalaya.</placeName>
                    </hi>
                    <note place="right" hand="#author">
                        <ref xml:id="ed_ytm_3mg_hy" type="siglum" target="#Geographie_der_Pflanzen_D">D.</ref>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <p>Observations <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">de</del>
                        <add place="intralinear">sur</add>
                    </subst> la géographie des plantes <lb/>par le <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/v8/H0013583">Docteur
                            <hi rendition="#uu">George Govan</hi>
                    </persName> (entre les
                    <lb/>rivières <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/1252798">Jumna</placeName> et <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">Sutledge</del>
                        <add place="intralinear">
                            <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/1115006">Sutledge</placeName>
                        </add>
                    </subst>.)<supplied cert="high">.</supplied>
                    <bibl corresp="https://edition-humboldt.de/v8/VWSWNKTG">
                        <lb/>
                        <choice>
                            <abbr>
                                <hi rendition="#u">Edinb.</hi>
                            </abbr>
                            <expan>
                                <hi rendition="#u">Edinburgh</hi>
                            </expan>
                        </choice>
                        <hi rendition="#u"> </hi>
                        <choice>
                            <abbr>
                                <hi rendition="#u">Journ.</hi>
                            </abbr>
                            <expan>
                                <hi rendition="#u">Journal</hi>
                            </expan>
                        </choice>
                        <hi rendition="#u"> of Science </hi>
                        <choice>
                            <abbr>
                                <hi rendition="#u">Jan.</hi>
                            </abbr>
                            <expan>
                                <hi rendition="#u">January</hi>
                            </expan>
                        </choice>
                        <hi rendition="#u"> 1825. </hi>
                        <choice>
                            <abbr>
                                <hi rendition="#u">p.</hi>
                            </abbr>
                            <expan>
                                <hi rendition="#u">page</hi>
                            </expan>
                        </choice>
                        <hi rendition="#u"> 17.</hi>
                    </bibl>
                </p>
                <note place="right" hand="#author" rend="sticked">
                    <pb n="26r" facs="http://content.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de/dms/PPN838243592/1200/0/00000053.jpg"/>Le cryptogame que l’on croit <supplied cert="high">être</supplied>
                    <lb/>la cause de la neige rouge <lb/>a été découvert récemment <lb/>aussi en
                        <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/2661886">Suède</placeName>
                    <lb/>par <persName ref="http://d-nb.info/gnd/118643959">Agardh</persName>
                    <supplied cert="high">.</supplied>
                    <pb n="26v" facs="http://content.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de/dms/PPN838243592/1200/0/00000054.jpg"/>
                    <gap unit="pages" quantity="1" reason="empty"/>
                </note>
                <p>Les <choice>
                        <sic>pleines</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">plaines</corr>
                </choice> de la partie Nord<supplied cert="high">-</supplied>ouest de <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/1114958">l’Indostan</placeName>
                    <lb/>ne <choice>
                        <sic>s’ébuent</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">s’ébouent</corr>
                    </choice> jusqu’à <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/1257806">Saharanpore</placeName> encore
                    <lb/>que de <measure quantity="800" unit="foot">800</measure> ou <measure quantity="1000" unit="foot">1000 pieds anglais</measure>.</p>
                <p>Les parties humides sont couvertes d’espèces <lb/>gigantesques de
                        Saccharum<supplied cert="high">,</supplied> dans lesquelles <lb/>les
                    éléphans se tiennent pendant la <lb/>saison des pluies<supplied cert="high">,</supplied> surtout autour de <lb/>
                    <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/1257806">Padshahmuhul</placeName>, jadis séjour <choice>
                        <sic>favorit</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">favori</corr>
                    </choice>
                    <lb/>des Empereurs de <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/1273294">Delhi</placeName>.</p>
                <p>Les <choice>
                        <sic>pleines</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">plaines</corr>
                    </choice> plus sèches (toujours au<supplied cert="high">-</supplied>dessous
                    <lb/>de <measure quantity="1000" unit="foot">1000 pieds</measure>) ont une
                    physionomie <lb/>africaine. En <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/6255146">Afrique</placeName>
                    <supplied cert="high">,</supplied> c’est l’asclepias
                    <lb/>gigantea et Rhamnus Lotus, ici<supplied cert="high">,</supplied> c’est
                    <lb/>l’asclepias syriaca et Ziziphus <lb/>jujuba, qui <choice>
                        <sic>caractérise</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">caractérisent</corr>
                    </choice> la végétation. <lb/>Les petites collines sont couvertes <lb/>de
                    Barberia <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">B</del>
                        <add place="intralinear">prionitis</add>
                    </subst> et Capparis <lb/>
                    <choice>
                        <sic>heteroclyta</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">heteroclita</corr>
                    </choice>, Salvadora persica <add place="superlinear">et</add> plusieurs
                        <lb/>
                    <pb n="27v" facs="http://content.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de/dms/PPN838243592/1200/0/00000056.jpg"/>Mimoses, <choice>
                        <abbr>M.</abbr>
                        <expan>Mimosa</expan>
                    </choice> Seerissa, arabica, <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">et</del>
                        <lb/>
                        <add place="intralinear">
                            <choice>
                                <sic>farnesiana</sic>
                                <corr cert="high">farnesiaca</corr>
                            </choice>
                        </add>
                    </subst> et Catechu, de <choice>
                        <sic>Boutea</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">Butea</corr>
                    </choice>
                    <lb/>frondosa, et surtout de <choice>
                        <sic>Capparis</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">Caparis</corr>
                    </choice> aphylla, <lb/>et le superbe Pergularia odoratissima. <lb/>Le Pinus
                    longifolia de <persName ref="http://d-nb.info/gnd/117598275">
                        <choice>
                            <abbr>Roxb.</abbr>
                            <expan>Roxburgh</expan>
                        </choice>
                    </persName> est encore <lb/>très rare.</p>
                <p>En s’élevant de <measure quantity="1000" unit="foot">1000</measure> à <measure quantity="3000" unit="foot">3000 pieds</measure>
                    <supplied cert="high">,</supplied>
                    <lb/>on commence à trouver <add place="superlinear">des forêts</add> de Shorea
                    <lb/>robusta, de Dalbergia Sissoo, de <lb/>Murraya exotica, de Gmelina arborea,
                    <lb/>sur lesquelles <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">rappen rap</del>
                        <add place="intralinear">
                            <choice>
                                <sic>rempent</sic>
                                <corr>rampent</corr>
                            </choice>
                        </add>
                    </subst>
                    <lb/>le Hastingia coccinea, des Echites et <lb/>des Smilax. Au<supplied cert="high">-</supplied>dessus de <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">350</del>
                        <add place="intralinear">
                            <measure quantity="3500" unit="foot">3500</measure>
                        </add>
                    </subst>
                    <measure quantity="3500" unit="foot"> pieds</measure>
                    <supplied cert="high">,</supplied>
                    <lb/>
                    <choice>
                        <abbr>p.</abbr>
                        <expan>par</expan>
                    </choice>
                    <choice>
                        <abbr>e.</abbr>
                        <expan>exemple</expan>
                    </choice> près de <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/1262151">la ville de
                        Nahn</placeName>
                    <supplied cert="high">,</supplied>
                    <lb/>le Pinus longifolia, <add place="left">
                        <metamark/>que les indigènes
                        <lb/>appellent <lb/>Cheer, et <lb/>deux espèces de Chênes<note place="mBottom" hand="#author">2 species welche die Eingebohrenen nen̅en
                            <hi rendition="#u">Ban</hi> und <hi rendition="#u">Mohroo</hi>.</note>
                    </add>
                    <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">prend son</del>
                        <add place="intralinear">prennent leur</add>
                    </subst>
                    <lb/>plus grand <choice>
                        <sic>dévelloppement</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">développement</corr>
                    </choice>. <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">
                            <gap unit="words" quantity="1" reason="illegible"/>
                        </del>
                        <add place="intralinear">
                            <lb/>C’est</add>
                    </subst> là que <choice>
                        <sic>végète</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">végètent</corr>
                    </choice> Andromeda <lb/>ovalifolia <persName ref="http://d-nb.info/gnd/117126314">
                        <choice>
                            <abbr>Wall.</abbr>
                            <expan>Wallich</expan>
                        </choice>
                    </persName>
                    <supplied cert="high">,</supplied> Morus serrata, Rho-<lb/>dodendron puniceum, Rubia <choice>
                        <sic>munjet</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">munjeet</corr>
                    </choice>, <lb/>des Berberis et des Crataegus à <lb/>forme entièrement
                        <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/6255148">européenne</placeName>. Le <lb/>Pinus deodora ne
                    se montre que sur des <lb/>
                    <del rendition="#s">plus hauts</del> sommets de
                        <measure quantity="7000" unit="foot">7000</measure> à <measure quantity="8000" unit="foot">8000 pieds</measure>. </p>
                <p>
                    <add place="left">
                        <choice>
                            <orig>dans</orig>
                            <reg>Dans</reg>
                        </choice> les ravins<supplied cert="high">,</supplied> on trouve <lb/>encore
                        Habenaria gi-<lb/>gantea et pectinata.</add>
                </p>
            </div>
